{{Infobox Artwork | image_file=Andrea Mantegna 036.jpg | title=Agony in the Garden | artist=Andrea Mantegna | year= 1458-1460 | medium=oil on panel | height_metric=63 | width_metric=80 | metric_unit=cm | imperial_unit=in | museum=[[National Gallery]], [[London]] }} '''''Agony in the Garden''''' is a painting by the Italian artist [[Andrea Mantegna]] between 1458 and 1460. It is conserved at the [[National Gallery]] in [[London]].
Mantegna's brother-in-law, Renaissance artist [[Giovanni Bellini]], is considered to have been inspired by this painting for his own rendering of ''Agony in the Garden,'' painted between 1460 and 1465. Both paintings are conserved at the [[National Gallery]] in [[London]].
